}
  IDEP2TD.SYS [/R]

This command installs a driver for a
hardware real-time clock. It works
with the PBI device IDE Plus 2.

Using the /R option installs a
read-only version that requires less
memory.

If this driver is the first resident
program, a smaller version can be
installed to save memory.

The last character in the status line
shows which driver is active:
W - read and write driver
w - smaller read and write driver
R - read-only driver
r - smaller read-only driver
